COMMERCIAL LOAN AGREEMENT

This Commercial Loan Agreement ("Agreement") is made as of March 1, 2024 between FirstBank Commercial NA ("Lender") and BorrowerCo LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("Borrower").

1. LOAN
1.1 Amount. Lender agrees to lend Borrower up to Ten Million Dollars ($10,000,000) (the "Loan").
1.2 Purpose. Borrower shall use Loan proceeds solely for working capital and general corporate purposes.
1.3 Term. The Loan matures on March 1, 2027 (the "Maturity Date").

2. INTEREST AND PAYMENTS
2.1 Interest Rate. The Loan shall bear interest at SOFR plus 375 basis points per annum, adjusted quarterly.
2.2 Default Rate. Upon default, interest shall accrue at an additional 500 basis points.
2.3 Payments. Interest is payable monthly. Principal is due at maturity.
2.4 Prepayment. Borrower may prepay subject to a prepayment penalty of 3% in Year 1, 2% in Year 2, and 1% in Year 3.

3. CONDITIONS PRECEDENT
Lender's obligation to fund is subject to:
(a) Execution of Loan Documents;
(b) Perfection of Collateral;
(c) No Material Adverse Change;
(d) Satisfactory due diligence;
(e) Receipt of legal opinion.

4. REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES
Borrower represents and warrants:
(a) Organization: Borrower is duly organized and in good standing.
(b) Authority: Borrower has authority to enter into this Agreement.
(c) No Conflicts: This Agreement does not conflict with other agreements.
(d) Financial Statements: All financial statements are accurate and complete.
(e) Litigation: No material litigation is pending or threatened.
(f) Taxes: All taxes have been paid.
(g) Compliance: Borrower is in compliance with all laws.
(h) No Default: No default exists under any material agreement.
(i) Material Adverse Change: No MAC has occurred since the date of financial statements.

5. AFFIRMATIVE COVENANTS
Borrower shall:
(a) Provide quarterly financial statements within 45 days of quarter end;
(b) Provide annual audited financial statements within 90 days of year end;
(c) Maintain insurance satisfactory to Lender;
(d) Pay all taxes when due;
(e) Maintain books and records;
(f) Permit Lender inspections upon request;
(g) Notify Lender of any default or litigation.

6. FINANCIAL COVENANTS
Borrower shall maintain:
(a) Minimum Fixed Charge Coverage Ratio of 1.25:1.00 tested quarterly;
(b) Maximum Total Leverage Ratio of 3.50:1.00 tested quarterly;
(c) Minimum Tangible Net Worth of $5,000,000;
(d) Minimum Liquidity of $1,000,000.

7. NEGATIVE COVENANTS
Without Lender's consent, Borrower shall not:
(a) Incur additional indebtedness exceeding $250,000;
(b) Grant liens on any assets;
(c) Dispose of material assets;
(d) Make acquisitions exceeding $500,000;
(e) Pay dividends or make distributions;
(f) Change business operations materially;
(g) Enter into transactions with affiliates except at arm's length;
(h) Amend organizational documents.

8. COLLATERAL
8.1 Grant. Borrower grants Lender a first priority security interest in all of Borrower's assets, including:
(a) Accounts receivable;
(b) Inventory;
(c) Equipment;
(d) Intellectual property;
(e) General intangibles;
(f) All proceeds thereof.
8.2 Further Assurances. Borrower shall execute any documents necessary to perfect Lender's security interest.

9. EVENTS OF DEFAULT
The following constitute Events of Default:
(a) Failure to pay principal or interest when due;
(b) Breach of any representation or warranty;
(c) Breach of any covenant;
(d) Cross-default under any other indebtedness exceeding $100,000;
(e) Judgment against Borrower exceeding $250,000;
(f) Insolvency or bankruptcy;
(g) Change of control;
(h) Material Adverse Change.

10. REMEDIES
Upon Event of Default, Lender may:
(a) Declare all amounts immediately due and payable;
(b) Exercise remedies under the UCC;
(c) Take possession of Collateral;
(d) Apply Collateral proceeds to obligations.

11. EXPENSES AND INDEMNIFICATION
11.1 Expenses. Borrower shall pay all costs of this Agreement, including legal fees.
11.2 Indemnification. Borrower shall indemnify Lender from all claims arising from this Agreement.

12. GOVERNING LAW
This Agreement is governed by New York law.

FIRSTBANK COMMERCIAL NA
By: _________________________

BORROWERCO LLC
By: _________________________
